cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.CV, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with secure transmission of images using DNA sequences and encryption techniques. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Information theory is closely related to cryptography and this paper involves the use of DNA sequences for encryption which can be considered as a form of information theory. 
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - This category deals with computational methods for solving problems in various fields including cryptography. The paper involves the use of computational methods for encryption and transmission of images. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - This category deals with image processing and analysis which is relevant to the topic of image transmission in this paper. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - This category deals with multimedia systems and applications which includes image transmission. The paper involves the use of encryption techniques for secure transmission of images which can be considered as a multimedia application.
